CGoal

Fill a blank grid (like 5√ó5, 10√ó10, or bigger) using numerical clues given along each row and column. When solved correctly, the filled cells reveal a hidden pixel art image (e.g., heart, smiley, tree).

üéÆ Mechanics

Grid setup

Grid size: N √ó N (e.g., 10√ó10).

Each row and column has a sequence of numbers.

Example: A row clue 3 1 means ‚Üí 3 filled cells, then at least one empty, then 1 filled cell.

Player actions

Click/tap to mark a cell filled (black).

Right-click/long-press to mark a cell as empty (X).

Leave unmarked if undecided.

Logic solving

Players cross-check row and column clues.

Must ensure all constraints match simultaneously.

No guessing ideally ‚Äî pure logic leads to solution.

Validation

Game auto-checks if rows/columns match clues.

Puzzle ends when all conditions are satisfied ‚Üí hidden pixel-art revealed üéâ.

‚öôÔ∏è Features / Variations

Puzzle Sizes: Easy 5√ó5 ‚Üí Challenging 20√ó20+.

Themes: Reveal animals, logos, retro icons.

Modes:

Classic: No time pressure.

Timed: Solve under countdown.

Daily Puzzle: New nonogram each day.

Helpers: Autofill definite cells, highlight errors, hint system.

Scoring: Based on time, hints used, mistakes made.

üß† Skills / Appeal

Pure logic puzzle (like Sudoku).

Relaxing yet brain-stimulating.

Satisfaction of revealing hidden image as reward.

